gamespot tfsoftware\" />\n* Launched as part of ''The Orange Box''<ref name=\"eurogamer orange box date\" />\n* Transitioned into a [[free-to-play]] game in June 2011<ref name=\"develop tf2 f2p\" />\n}}\n{{Video game titles/item\n| article = The Orange Box\n| title = The Orange Box\n| date = {{Video game release|WW|October 10, 2007}}\n| refs = <ref name=\"eurogamer orange box date\" />\n| release = {{Unbulleted list|2007 \u2013 Windows, Xbox 360, PlayStation 3<ref name=\"eurogamer orange box date\" /><ref name=\"eurogamer orange box ps3\" />}}\n| notes =\n* A compilation including ''Half-Life 2'', ''Half-Life 2: Episode One'', ''Half-Life 2: Episode Two'', ''Portal'', and ''Team Fortress 2''<ref name=\"eurogamer orange box date\" />\n* Ported to PlayStation 3 by [[Electronic Arts]]<ref name=\"ign orange box ps3 port\" />\n}}\n{{Video game titles/item\n| article = Counter-Strike Online\n| title = Counter-Strike Online\n| date = {{Video game release|KOR|January 2008|TW|July 2008|CHN|November 2008|JP|August 2009}}\n| refs = <ref name=\"nexon 2008\" /><ref name=\"nexon 2009\" />\n| release = {{Unbulleted list|2008 \u2013 Windows<ref name=\"nexon 2008\" />}}\n| notes =\n* Collaboration with [[Nexon]]<ref name=\"engadget cso2\" />\n}}\n{{Video game titles/item\n| article = Left 4 Dead\n| title = Left 4 Dead\n| date = {{Video game release|WW|November 17, 2008}}\n| refs = <ref name=\"arstech l4d demo\" />\n| release = {{Unbulleted list|2008 \u2013 Windows, Xbox 360<ref name=\"eurogamer l4d demo\" />|2010 \u2013 Mac OS X<ref name=\"shacknews l4d mac\" />}}\n| notes =\n* [[Cooperative gameplay|Cooperative]] [[first-person shooter]] set in a zombie apocalypse<ref name=\"eurogamer l4d demo\" />\n* Developed by [[Turtle Rock Studios]], who were acquired by Valve prior to the release of ''Left 4 Dead''<ref name=\"gamespot turtle rock\" />\n}}\n{{Video game titles/item\n| article = Left 4 Dead 2\n| title = Left 4 Dead 2\n| date = {{Video game release|WW|November 17, 2009}}\n| refs